    en: "Debt collectors work under strict rules. They cannot call at odd hours. They cannot threaten arrest. They cannot contact an employer once told to stop. They cannot lie about the amount owed. They cannot use abusive language. The federal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (15 USC 1692) and New York General Business Law 601 give consumers tools to stop harassment — including the right to demand in writing that all contact stop, and the right to sue for statutory damages of up to $1,000 plus attorney's fees."
